Package: Endo
Type: Package
Title: Downstream Data Analysis Functions for NGS and Microscopy Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Erik", "Larsen",
                    email = "eriklarsen@arizona.edu",
                    role = c("cre", "aut"),
                    comment =  c(ORCID = '0000-0002-5878-1538')))
Maintainer: Erik Larsen <eriklarsen@arizona.edu>
Description: Documentation of IPMS-MS data wrangling in TSC format obtained from
  University of Arizona's College of Molecular Medicine's Orbitrap. IPMS-MS data
  is "post-discovery" of all peptide-ion fragments-- fragments were
  statistically assigned parent peptides and queried against protein sequence
  databases; number of spectra uniquely identified as belonging to a given
  protein were quantified as total spectral counts. TSCs were used for
  downstream analysis. Package also documents confocal fluorescence microscopy
  data wrangling and statistical analysis. Package relies on a lab-developed
  package with functions to more easily identify biologically meaningful results
  of downstream analyses of lists of genes/proteins obtained from NGS analysis.
